pullRequest.title: Move verifyQualifiedName to internalFindClassString
pullRequest.bodyText:
The intention is to move verifyQualifiedName to internalFindClassString
so as to call hashClassTableAtString before verifyQualifiedName
to avoid verifying duplicate classes.
Signed-off-by: Cheng Jin jincheng@ca.ibm.com

nodes.bodyText: This needs documenting to show that it is a bitfield. To reinforce this, CLASSNAME_VALID should be the bit OR of the other two values, rather than being defined directly to 3.
The parameter name is confusing. Please rename it and change the documentation to indicate that it is the set of allowed bits.
nodes.diffHunk:
@@ -356,12 +356,13 @@ internalCreateArrayClass(J9VMThread* vmThread, J9ROMArrayClass* romClass, J9Clas
  * @param className String object representing name of the class to load
  * @param classLoader J9ClassLoader to use
  * @param options load options such as J9_FINDCLASS_FLAG_EXISTING_ONLY
+ * @param expectedReturnCode the expected return code to the caller

@@ -3115,10 +3116,11 @@ getStringUTF8Length(J9VMThread *vmThread,j9object_t string);
 *
 * @param[in] *vmThread current thread
 * @param[in] string the class name string
+* @param[in] expectedReturnCode the expected return code to the caller

nodes.bodyText: Please either use a goto or nest the other code inside the if here to avoid multiple return.
Though it doesn't matter in practice, the parameters in the macro should really be reversed.

This actually adds a call to verifyQualifiedName that wasn't there before. It likely doesn't matter, but could be fixed by adding CLASSNAME_INVALID as an input value to findClassString (i.e. check for this value in there and don't do the verification).
nodes.diffHunk:
@@ -556,7 +556,8 @@ JVM_FindLoadedClass(JNIEnv* env, jobject classLoader, jobject className)
 			NULL,
 			J9_JNI_UNWRAP_REFERENCE(className),
 			vmClassLoader,
-			J9_FINDCLASS_FLAG_EXISTING_ONLY);
+			J9_FINDCLASS_FLAG_EXISTING_ONLY,
+			CLASSNAME_VALID);

nodes.diffHunk:
@@ -356,12 +356,14 @@ internalCreateArrayClass(J9VMThread* vmThread, J9ROMArrayClass* romClass, J9Clas

  * @param classLoader J9ClassLoader to use

+ *        including CLASSNAME_VALID_NON_ARRARY, CLASSNAME_VALID_ARRARY, or CLASSNAME_VALID.

nodes.bodyText: Please add a bit of doc here saying these are bit values.
